examples.text: „MSDN's primary Web presence at msdn.microsoft.com is a collection of sites for the developer community that provide information, documentation, and discussion that is authored both by Microsoft and by the community at large. Recently, Microsoft has placed emphasis on incorporation of forums, blogs, library annotations and social bookmarking to make MSDN an open dialog with the developer community rather than a one-way service.“
examples.translation: MSDNs erste Webpräsenz bei msdn.microsoft.com ist eine Sammlung von Seiten für die Entwickler-Community, die Informationen, Dokumente und Diskussionen, welche sowohl bei Microsoft als auch bei der Community in seiner Gesamtheit verfasst wird. Vor Kurzem hat Microsoft die Einbindung von Foren, Blogs, Bibliotheksanmerkungen und sozialen Lesezeichen hervorgehoben, um MSDN zu einem offenen Dialog der Entwickler-Community werden zu lassen, statt es als einen Einweg-Service zu betreiben.

examples.text: „MSDN's primary Web presence at msdn.microsoft.com is a collection of sites for the developer community that provide information, documentation, and discussion that is authored both by Microsoft and by the community at large. Recently, Microsoft has placed emphasis on incorporation of forums, blogs, library annotations and social bookmarking to make MSDN an open dialog with the developer community rather than a one-way service.“
examples.translation: „msdn.microsoft.com'daki MSDN'nin aslî Web varlığı hem Microsoft, hem de geliştirici topluluk tarafından yazılan ve geliştirici topluluk için bilgi, belgeleme, tartışma [alanı] sağlayan bir siteler koleksiyonudur. Son zamanlarda Microsoft forumlar, bloglar, kütüphane ek açıklamaları ve sosyal sahife işaretlemenin dahil edilmesine önem vererek MSDN'i geliştirici toplulukla tek yönlü hizmet yerine açık iletişim hâline getirmek istedi.“
